OpenVPN Cookbook Chapter 5 sample code

The samples in this chapter are openvpn configuration files, 
as well as some helper scripts.

Chapter 5 is divided up into 10 recipes. Below is a list of which
configuration file is used in which recipe.

5.1 Using a Client-side up/down script
server: example5-1-server.conf
client: example5-1.ovpn
script: updown.bat

5.2 Using a 'client-connect' script
server: example5-2-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.ovpn
script: example5-2-connect.sh

5.3 Using a 'learn-address' script
server: example5-3-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.ovpn
script: example5-3-learn-address.sh

5.4 Using a 'tls-verify' script
server: example5-4-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.ovpn
scripts: example5-4-tls-verify.sh, example5-4-tls-verify.sh.allowed

5.5 Using a 'auth-user-pass-verify' script
server: example5-5-server.conf
client: example5-5-client.conf
scripts: example5-5-aupv.sh, example5-5-aupv.sh.passwd

5.6 Script order
server: example5-6-server.conf
client: example5-5-client.conf
script: example5-6-script.sh

5.7 Script security and logging
server: example5-1-server.conf
client: example5-7-client.conf
script: example5-7-up.sh

5.8 Scripting and IPv6
server: example5-8-server.conf
client: example5-8-client.conf
script: example5-8-script.sh

5.9 Using the 'down-root' plugin
server: example5-9-server.conf
script: example5-9.sh

5.10 Using the PAM authentication plugin
server: example5-10-server.conf
client: example5-10.ovpn
